a sad triumph of greed over quality bep was one of my favorite hip-hop acts of the late 90 's . their debut album `` behind the front '' and even their sophomore album `` bridging the gap '' continued a musical approach and ideology more akin to tribe called quest , talib kweli , de la soul , and the roots than the current gangster rap trend . after this however , bep apparently figured out that they can make more money with intellectually depraved dance tracks than they can with original music . and it 's a shame . money business is a perfect example of an album crafted from bottom to top for pop appeal . in 2004 ( with elephunk ) bep left the artistic music community and joined the commercial music community . it was sad to see them go